column1: On each trial of this task, you will see two images on the left and right side of the computer screen, like below.
Your job is to memorize that the image pairs go together. You can use any strategy to remember them.
For example, you could rehearse them in your memory, or link them through a story.
It's important that you remember that these images go together. Your memory will later be tested.
Get ready to see a series of image pairs!
Each pair of images will only last on the screen for a few sceonds, so pay attention!
When you're ready to start the game, press space!
Great job! Your memory for each image pair will now be tested.
You will first see one image on the computer screen, like below. You will be asked to bring to mind the associated image pair.
In this situation, you would try to remember the book.
Immediately after, you will be shown three other images, like this. You should select the image that was previously associated with the image you just saw.
The response options are below each image. In this case, you should press 'J' to indicate that the book was previously paired with the woman, Jessica Alba.
Try to chose the correct response as quickly as you can! Put your right hand on the keyboard and get ready to press 'J', K"
These keyboard options will remain on the screen under each image as a reminder throughout the task.
When you're ready to start the game, press space!
